#@
The function applies the function 'func' to each element of 'container' and returns true if every application of 'func' returned true, otherwise false.
The function executes 'func' until the result can be determined.
The function returns 'default' if the container is empty.
The function may use 'func' only for calling.
In indexed arrays, the order of taking elements to apply 'func' is from beginning to end.

signature:
fn (string:@string, default:@bool, func:fn(@char)@bool) @bool
fn (array:@byte_array, default:@bool, func:fn(@byte)@bool) @bool
fn (container:.core_all, default:@bool, func:fn(any)) @bool
fn (container:([obj item:common]|[table param(hash:arg) = item:common]|[set item:param(hash:arg)]|[array item:common*]), default:@bool, func:fn($item)@bool) @bool
@#
fn all(container, default, func) null

#@
The function is analogous to the function 'all', but 'func' takes both the key (index) and the value.
The function cannot be applied to a set.

