:nan_cmp   - if during comparison of arg_1 and arg_2, a comparison of two constants of type 'float' occurred, but one of them is not a number (nan).
If the arguments of the function have the type @set, @table or @obj (not .core_cmp), they are compared only for equality/inequality. (:equal, :not_equal)
