The function returns :invalid_str_fmt if 'num' does not contain a number in the specified numeral system.
The function returns :64_bits_is_not_enough if 64 bits are not enough to store the resulting number.
     Positive numbers are treated as unsigned, i.e., the function will return -1 if 'num' == "18446744073709551615" and 'base' == 10,
     since 64 bits are enough to store the unsigned number 18446744073709551615.
     However, for numbers 18446744073709551616 or -9223372036854775809, 64 bits are no longer enough.

