      |the symbols + and - are allowed before the values                                                                        |"1.0e-4" -> 0.0001
      |allows writing integer numbers (without a fractional part)                                                               |"+12.5"  -> 12.5
      |special values may also be specified: "nan", "inf"                                                                       |"-12"    -> -12.0
      |excluding special values, only the following characters are allowed: 0-9 . e + -                                         |"NAn"    -> not a number
      |if a character in the string is a letter, its case does not matter                                                       |"+1200"  -> 1200.0
byte  |converts a number from byte type to float type                                                                           |0b0a     -> 10.0
int   |converts a number from int type to float type                                                                            |-15      -> -15.0
float |no conversion needed                                                                                                     |102.25   -> 102.25

