#@
The function converts a constant to its textual representation.
The function works with a string not as an array of characters.
The function treats 'null' as a value, not as its absence.
Conversion rules:
Type      |Result                                                                                          |Example
----------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------------------
string    |argument                                                                                        |"10"                                      -> "10"
null      |as the value would be written in source code                                                    |null                                      -> "null"
token     |as the value would be written in source code, but without :                                     |:123                                      -> "123"
bool      |as the value would be written in source code                                                    |false                                     -> "false"
byte      |as the value would be written in source code, but without 0b                                    |0bfe                                      -> "fe"
char      |string with the specified character                                                             |'z'                                       -> "z"
int       |string with the specified number in the decimal system, without the + symbol                    |123                                       -> "123"
byte_array|string with bytes converted in sequence, without separators                                     |[byte_array 0b00, 0b01, 0b02]             -> "000102"
time      |dd.MM.yyyy hh.mm.ss timezone                                                                    |assemble_time(0, 2010, 8, 13, 23, 14, 57) -> "14.08.2010 02:14:57 +3.00"
          |Where:                                                                                          |
          |     d        - day                                                                             |
          |     M        - month                                                                           |
          |     y        - year                                                                            |
          |     h        - hour                                                                            |
          |     m        - minute                                                                          |
          |     s        - second                                                                          |
          |     timezone - the number of hours added to UTC,                                               |
          |                     so that the time in the string is local                                    |
float     |string with the specified number as a decimal fraction, without the + symbol                    |1.0                                       -> "1.0"
          |maximum number of digits after the decimal point - 15                                           |1.0/3.0                                   -> "0.333333333333333"
          |special values: nan, inf, -inf                                                                  |
box       |as the value would be written in source code, but to_string is applied to the elements          |[box 0b00, null]                          -> "[box 00, null]"
array     |as the value would be written in source code, but to_string is applied to the elements          |[array 0b00, :12]                         -> "[array 00, 12]"
obj       |as the value would be written in source code, but to_string is applied to the key and value     |[obj :12 = 0bff]                          -> "[obj 12 = ff]"
table     |as the value would be written in source code, but to_string is applied to the key and value     |[table :12 = 0bff]                        -> "[table 12 = ff]"
set       |as the value would be written in source code, but to_string is applied to the elements          |[set 0b00, :12]                           -> "[set 00, 12]"

